<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{6}{y}={19}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4}{x}-{5}{y}=-{17}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -4. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{-{{5}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{4}}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left(-{5}{x}+{6}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{4}}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left({19}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({4}\right)}{x}+{4.8}{y}={15.2}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}-{5}{y}=-{17}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.2}{y}=-{1.8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{1.8}}{{-{{0.2}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{6}{\left({9}\right)}={19}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({54}\right)}={19}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={19}-{\left({54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{35}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={7}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({7},{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

